article.description: Richmond Aririguzoh registered 18 points and three blocks as Princeton narrowly defeated Dartmouth 69-68 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Aririguzoh leads Princeton over Dartmouth 69-68
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Richmond Aririguzoh registered 18 points and three blocks as Princeton narrowly defeated Dartmouth 69-68 on Saturday night. Myles Stephens had 17 points and eight rebounds for Princeton (13-8, 5-3 Ivy League). Jaelin Llewellyn added 14 points. Devin Cannady had 10 points for the hosts. Brendan Barry had 26 points for the Big Green (11-13, 2-6). James Foye added 17 points. Chris Knight had 12 points. Princeton faces Cornell at home on Friday. Dartmouth takes on Yale on the road on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
